Description: Fix CVE-2025-49128 - misleading exception leaks unrelated buffer
 content when JsonParser is created from a byte[]/char[] with non-zero start
 offset. JsonLocation._appendSourceDesc reads from index 0 instead of the
 supplied offset, exposing up to 500 bytes/chars of unrelated buffer data
 in JsonParseException messages (CWE-209).
 .
 Backport for jackson-core 2.10.1: the upstream fix (jackson-core PR #652,
 commit a6c297682737dde13337cb7c3020f299518609a8, released in 2.13.0) relies
 on the ContentReference abstraction introduced in 2.13. ContentReference is
 not present in 2.10.1, so this backport instead slices the input array at
 the JsonFactory entry points (createParser(byte[],int,int) and
 createParser(char[],int,int)) so that IOContext._sourceRef only references
 the actual content range. JsonLocation then has nothing outside that range
 to expose. The upstream regression test (testContentSnippetWithOffset) and
 its a2q() helper are included verbatim and pass against this slice-based
 fix.
Origin: backport, https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson-core/commit/a6c297682737dde13337cb7c3020f299518609a8
Bug: https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson-core/pull/652
Bug-CVE: CVE-2025-49128
Forwarded: not-needed
Last-Update: 2026-06-18

